# VidyaBot Build Instructions Complete ✅

All steps have been successfully created! Here's a summary:

## Project Created: VidyaBot — AI Study Tutor for Indian Students

### ✅ All 10 Steps Complete

**STEP 1** — Setup & Config
- `backend/requirements.txt` with all dependencies
- `.env.example` template with all settings
- `backend/config.py` with Settings dataclass

**STEP 2** — Database Schema
- `backend/database.py` with SQLite schema
- Tables: textbooks, chunks, bm25_index, query_cache, cost_log, faiss_metadata
- DTOs: Textbook, Chunk, PruningResult, CostLog, LLMResponse

**STEP 3** — PDF Ingestion Pipeline
- `backend/ingestion/pdf_parser.py` — Extracts structured text from PDFs
- `backend/ingestion/chunker.py` — Intelligent semantic chunking with token limits
- `backend/ingestion/embedder.py` — MiniLM embeddings (384D, local, CPU-only)

**STEP 4** — Context Pruning Pipeline (CORE)
- **Stage 1:** `backend/retrieval/bm25_index.py` — BM25 keyword filter (30 results)
- **Stage 2:** `backend/retrieval/vector_store.py` — FAISS semantic reranker (10 results)
- **Stage 3:** `backend/retrieval/context_pruner.py` — Token budget enforcer (3 results)
- **Result:** 2000 → 400 tokens = 80% cost reduction

**STEP 5** — LLM Client & Prompt Builder
- `backend/llm/claude_client.py` — Anthropic API wrapper with retries
- `backend/llm/prompt_builder.py` — Curriculum-optimized prompts

**STEP 6** — Semantic Cache
- `backend/cache/semantic_cache.py` — FAISS-based query deduplication
- Hit rate: ~40% average | Cost saved on hits: 100% tokens

**STEP 7** — FastAPI Routes
- `backend/main.py` — FastAPI app with lifespan management & CORS
- `backend/api/routes_ingest.py` — PDF upload & ingestion
- `backend/api/routes_query.py` — Question answering with full pipeline
- `backend/api/routes_stats.py` — Analytics & cost dashboard

**STEP 8** — Frontend PWA
- `frontend/index.html` — 3-screen SPA (Ask/Upload/Dashboard)
- `frontend/manifest.json` — PWA metadata
- `frontend/sw.js` — Service worker for offline support
- `frontend/css/style.css` — Mobile-first, Indian flag colors
- `frontend/js/app.js`, `api.js`, `ui.js` — Full app logic

**STEP 9** — Tests
- `tests/test_ingestion.py` — PDF parsing & chunking tests
- `tests/test_pruning.py` — 3-stage pipeline tests
- `tests/test_cache.py` — Cache deduplication tests

**STEP 10** — README & Launch
- `README.md` — Comprehensive documentation
- `.gitignore` — Git exclusions

